The paper deals with the retrieval of watermarks from images of 3D printed objects using a deep neural network. This involves image processing, computer vision, and machine learning techniques, which are all covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of synthetic data for training the network also falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also discusses the statistical operations applied on the confidence map generated by the neural network, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the generalization power of the network, which is related to the performance of the network on previously unseen data, and falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
